devdoc.details: Originally based on code of ERC20 by openzeppelin-solidity v2.1.2  https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/blob/v2.1.2/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20.sol

params._owner: address The address which owns the funds.
params._spender: address The address which will spend the funds.

allowance(address,address).return: A uint specifying the amount of ETH still available for the spender.

approve(address,uint256).details: Beware that changing an allowance with this method brings the risk that someone may use both the old  and the new allowance by unfortunate transaction ordering. One possible solution to mitigate this  race condition is to first reduce the spender's allowance to 0 and set the desired value afterwards:  https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/20#issuecomment-263524729

params._spender: The address which will spend the funds.
params._value: The amount of ETH to be spent.

params._owner: The address to query the balance of.

balanceOf(address).return: An uint representing the amount owned by the passed address.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: approve should be called when allowed[msg.sender][spender] == 0. To decrement  allowed value is better to use this function to avoid 2 calls (and wait until  the first transaction is mined)  From MonolithDAO Token.sol  Emits an Approval event.

params._spender: The address which will spend the funds.
params._subtractedValue: The amount of ETH to decrease the allowance by.

params._receiver: the address ETH is deposited to

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: approve should be called when allowed[msg.sender][spender] == 0. To increment  allowed value is better to use this function to avoid 2 calls (and wait until  the first transaction is mined)  From MonolithDAO Token.sol  Emits an Approval event.

params._addedValue: The amount of ETH to increase the allowance by.
params._spender: The address which will spend the funds.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Note that while this function emits an Approval event, this is not required as per the specification.

params._from: The address which you want to transfer ETH from
params._to: The address which you want to transfer to
params._value: the amount of ETH to be transferred

params._from: The address which you want to transfer ETH from
params._value: the amount of ETH to be transferred
params._walletAddr: CelerWallet address which should have a depositETH(bytes32) payable API
params._walletId: id of the wallet you want to deposit ETH into

params._value: the amount of ETH to withdraw
